&lt;h2 id="if-we-ask-chatgpt-directly"&gt;If we ask ChatGPT directly
&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;Hiss, a bit off. Let&amp;rsquo;s try gpt-5.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Prompt:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;img class="gallery-image" data-flex-basis="189px" data-flex-grow="78" height="1616" loading="lazy" sizes="(max-width: 767px) calc(100vw - 30px), (max-width: 1023px) 700px, (max-width: 1279px) 950px, 1232px" src="https://svtter.cn/p/%E7%AC%AC%E4%B8%89%E6%96%B9%E5%AE%A2%E6%88%B7%E7%AB%AF%E4%B8%8E%E5%A4%A7%E6%A8%A1%E5%9E%8B-api-%E7%BB%93%E5%90%88--%E6%80%A7%E8%83%BD%E5%B0%8F%E6%B5%8B/pics/wechat_2025-11-19_171536_131.png" srcset="https://svtter.cn/p/%E7%AC%AC%E4%B8%89%E6%96%B9%E5%AE%A2%E6%88%B7%E7%AB%AF%E4%B8%8E%E5%A4%A7%E6%A8%A1%E5%9E%8B-api-%E7%BB%93%E5%90%88--%E6%80%A7%E8%83%BD%E5%B0%8F%E6%B5%8B/pics/wechat_2025-11-19_171536_131_hu_431759ed555a584a.png 800w, https://svtter.cn/p/%E7%AC%AC%E4%B8%89%E6%96%B9%E5%AE%A2%E6%88%B7%E7%AB%AF%E4%B8%8E%E5%A4%A7%E6%A8%A1%E5%9E%8B-api-%E7%BB%93%E5%90%88--%E6%80%A7%E8%83%BD%E5%B0%8F%E6%B5%8B/pics/wechat_2025-11-19_171536_131.png 1275w" width="1275"&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="inference---reasons-for-poor-performance"&gt;Inference - Reasons for Poor Performance
&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Insufficient search capability. The Bocha API is to blame.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Different models may have different optimal hyperparameters for best performance. I called the large model API from Silicon Flow.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;h2 id="conclusion"&gt;Conclusion
&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;For this specific problem, ChatGPT still performs better. Compared to before, the official search + model combination also seems to perform better. Therefore, unless the data is particularly sensitive, it&amp;rsquo;s better to use the official service.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;This article is for reference only, just for fun.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>